3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex implements hourly funding rate settlements using a time-weighted average price mechanism across its 1-hour funding cycles. The exchange calculates funding rates based on the premium/discount between the perpetual contract price and the underlying spot index, with rates typically ranging from -0.75% to +0.75% per funding period. Portfolio margin allows traders to offset positions across different assets, reducing capital requirements for funding rate arbitrage strategies. Settlement occurs automatically through the StarkNet smart contract infrastructure."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","MKR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR's governance-driven volatility creates predictable funding rate patterns around key MakerDAO events like executive votes and collateral onboarding decisions. The token's institutional adoption and DeFi utility generate consistent trading interest, making funding rates more responsive to market sentiment. Paradex's self-custodial nature appeals to DeFi-native traders who prefer non-custodial exposure to governance tokens."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR funding rates on Paradex typically spike during major MakerDAO governance events, with rates reaching +0.5% hourly during contentious votes. The token shows strong correlation with broader DeFi sentiment, with funding rates turning negative during market downturns as shorts dominate. Seasonal patterns emerge around quarterly governance cycles, with elevated volatility in March, June, September, and December. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently arise due to Paradex's early-stage liquidity compared to centralized competitors."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR's limited availability on DEX perpetual platforms creates funding rate premiums on Paradex during high demand periods. Traders can capitalize on rate differentials between Paradex and major CEXs like Binance or OKX, particularly during governance events when CEX funding turns deeply negative. Portfolio margin enables efficient capital deployment across MKR positions and hedging instruments. The 1-hour funding frequency provides more granular profit-taking opportunities compared to 8-hour cycles on traditional exchanges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"StarkNet's relative novelty introduces smart contract and infrastructure risks not present on established Layer 1 platforms. MKR's governance-driven volatility can create rapid funding rate reversals that challenge position sizing decisions. Paradex's early-stage liquidity means wider spreads and potential slippage during volatile periods, affecting arbitrage profitability. Self-custodial requirements demand careful key management and understanding of StarkNet transaction mechanics to avoid operational losses."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Paradex's 1-hour funding cycle affect MKR arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The hourly cycle provides more frequent profit realization compared to traditional 8-hour periods, allowing traders to capture shorter-term governance-driven rate movements. However, it also requires more active monitoring and increases transaction frequency costs."},{"question":"What makes MKR funding rates unique on Paradex compared to other DEXs?","answer":"Paradex's institutional-grade infrastructure and Jump Trading pedigree attract sophisticated DeFi traders, creating different flow dynamics than retail-focused DEXs. The portfolio margin system also enables more complex cross-asset strategies involving MKR."},{"question":"How do MakerDAO governance events impact MKR funding rates on Paradex?","answer":"Executive votes, especially those involving collateral changes or stability fee adjustments, typically drive funding rates positive as long-biased DeFi participants increase leverage. Rate impacts can persist for 24-48 hours post-vote depending on outcome significance."},{"question":"What are the key risks of MKR funding arbitrage on StarkNet?","answer":"Primary risks include StarkNet network congestion during high activity periods, smart contract vulnerabilities in the early ecosystem, and the complexity of cross-layer arbitrage when hedging positions on Ethereum mainnet exchanges."}]}]
